    "name": "Firefox 5 - Custom Appmenu Button",
    "description": "A style that let's you completely control the look and feel of the appmenu button in Firefox 4+.",
    "additionalInfo": "-Don't like the colors given? Simply replace the xxxxxx on the line \"background-color: #xxxxxx !important;\" with your color (note: this line only shows up if you pick an option OTHER than transparent)\r\n-To use Terminus as the font, you need to download it from http://fractal.csie.org/~eric/wiki/Terminus_font\r\n-To use the Ubuntu font you need to download the font from http://font.ubuntu.com/\r\n\r\nTested on Windows 7/Vista with Firefox 4.0+\r\n\r\n4/25/11: Initial release\r\n5/9/11: Added silver, red, and blue color options\r\n5/10/11: Added box shadow options\r\n5/15/11: Added green color option\r\n6/1/11: Added purple color option and text style options\r\n6/2/11: Added orange color option and font choices\r\n6/4/11: Added border radius options\r\n6/5/11: Added border options\r\n6/15/11: Added text color options and gray background color options\r\n6/16/11: Added opacity and color options",
